data/target_archetypes.json — DEV/CURATION PLANNING ARTIFACT (Epic C-ii-a, #335)
================================================================================

WHAT THIS IS
------------
A curated list of ~80 (archetype, sector, threat_type, asset_class, threat_actor,
is_ot) target rows that the C-iii curation will author full library entries for.
It is the INPUT to the C-ii-b research sweep and the C-iii curation pass.

WHAT THIS IS NOT
----------------
This is NOT app-runtime seed data. The application does NOT load this file at
runtime. The canonical runtime seed library lives in:
  - data/seed_library_entries.json           (31 entries)
  - data/seed_library_entries_extension.json (13 entries)
This planning artifact is consumed only by Epic C-ii-b / C-iii tooling and humans
during curation (Arch-N2). Do not wire it into the seeding path.

ROW SCHEMA
----------
Each row is a JSON object:
  archetype      slug-style identifier for the target archetype
  sector         one of the 13 §3 core sectors (free string, NOT an enum):
                 manufacturing, energy_utilities, healthcare, financial_services,
                 retail_ecommerce, technology_saas, government_public, education,
                 professional_services, transportation_logistics, telecom,
                 hospitality, food_agriculture
  threat_type    a idraa.models.enums.ThreatCategory value
  asset_class    a idraa.models.enums.AssetClass value
  threat_actor   a idraa.models.enums.ThreatActorType value
  is_ot          bool — true if the row is OT-flavoured (OT threat type or
                 ot_systems/safety_systems asset class)
  keep_or_new    "keep" = sourced from an existing seed entry (carry existing_slug);
                 "new"  = a gap-filler the curation must author from scratch
  existing_slug  the seed slug for keep rows; null for new rows

PROVENANCE OF THE 44 "keep" ROWS
--------------------------------
The 44 keep rows mirror the existing seed entries. Their sector is the existing
entry's calibration_anchor.industry mapped to the nearest §3 core sector
(utilities/mining -> energy_utilities, information -> technology_saas,
professional/real_estate -> professional_services, public -> government_public,
financial -> financial_services, retail -> retail_ecommerce, transportation ->
transportation_logistics; healthcare/manufacturing/education map directly).

BALANCE GUARANTEE
-----------------
tests/unit/test_target_archetypes.py encodes the §3 coverage matrix and is the
real guard on this file. Every edit must keep it green:
  - 70-90 rows total
  - each of the 13 core sectors >=2 rows spanning >=2 threat types
  - each non-OT fill threat type (data_tampering, physical_tampering,
    denial_of_service, social_engineering, insider_misuse) >=2 rows
  - >=1 row each for asset classes people / facilities / business_process_revenue
    / business_process_cost / cash_or_equivalent
  - >=1 competitors threat-actor row
  - OT share <=30% of total
  - threat_type / asset_class / threat_actor are valid enum values
